<paragraph id="79085C0259665813588EC154FB8550C3" blockId="5.[174,1232,356,543]" pageId="5" pageNumber="322">
Species occurring locally in Europe, North Africa, 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C92596658135B43C154FA9C5003" box="[814,948,356,382]" name="Turkey" pageId="5" pageNumber="322">Asia Minor</collectingCountry>
and the Caucasus. Lives in the basidiomes of fungi of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BEB72781596658135AFCC1B4FAEE50E3" authority="M. P. Christ." authorityName="M. P. Christ." box="[657,966,388,415]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Pterulaceae" genus="Radulomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="322" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4BC38010596658135AFCC1B4FA0150E3" box="[657,809,388,414]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="322">Radulomyces</emphasis>
M.P. Christ.
</taxonomicName>
, mainly on deciduous trees (
<bibRefCitation id="1D2621F3596658135899C194F88A50C2" author="Reibnitz, J." box="[244,418,420,447]" pageId="5" pageNumber="322" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref7989" refString="Reibnitz, J. 1999. Verbreitung und Lebensraume der Baumschwammfresser Sudwestdeutschlands (Coleoptera: Cisidae). Mitteilungen Entomologischer Verein Stuttgart, 34, 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1999">Reibnitz, 1999</bibRefCitation>
), less often coniferous.
</paragraph>
